## Definitions

The **licensor** is the individual or entity offering these
terms, and the **software** is the software the licensor makes
available under these terms.

**You** refers to the individual or entity agreeing to these
terms.

**Your company** is any legal entity, sole proprietorship,
or other kind of organization that you work for, plus all
organizations that have control over, are under the control of,
or are under common control with that organization.  **Control**
means ownership of substantially all the assets of an entity,
or the power to direct its management and policies by vote,
contract, or otherwise.  Control can be direct or indirect.

**Your licenses** are all the licenses granted to you for the
software under these terms.

**Use** means anything you do with the software requiring one
of your licenses.

**Natural Person** means an individual human being.

**Government Entity** means any government body, state agency, ministry, military body,
law-enforcement body, municipal authority, or any person acting on their behalf.

**Military Use** means any use connected to weapons, targeting, military operations,
defense procurement, military simulation/training, or combat law-enforcement operations.

**Commercial Use** means any use intended for or resulting in commercial advantage
or monetary compensation.

**Legal Entity** means any company, corporation, startup, partnership, association, foundation,
institution, university, school, laboratory, NGO, government body, agency, or other juridical entity.

**Copyright Holders** means the persons or entities identified in copyright notices for the software.

**Required Notice** means any plain-text line beginning with `Required Notice:` provided by the licensor in NOTICE.

**Marks** means names, logos, trademarks, service marks, trade names, or branding identifiers of the licensors.

**Circumvention** means any direct or indirect attempt to avoid, bypass, or nullify restrictions in these terms.

**Permitted Purpose** means any use explicitly allowed by these terms and not otherwise prohibited by these terms.

**Complete Corresponding Source Code** means all source code, interface definition files, build scripts, and installation instructions necessary to generate, install, and run the modified software, excluding system libraries and generally available tools that are not part of the software.

**Military Bodies** means any armed forces, defense ministry, military command, military unit, intelligence service, paramilitary force, or any contractor acting on their behalf.

**Contributor** means any Natural Person or Legal Entity that submits a Contribution.

**Contribution** means any source code, object code, documentation, data, configuration, tests, scripts, issue attachments, patches, or other material intentionally submitted for inclusion in the software or project repositories.

**Submitted** means provided to the project by any channel used by the Copyright Holders, including pull requests, commits, patches, issue trackers, email, or other designated communication channels.

**Moral Rights** means rights of attribution, integrity, disclosure, withdrawal, and similar non-economic author rights, to the extent recognized by applicable law.
